params.markdown:
### Log manager

This dashboard provides visibility into the log management layer of Kafka clusters.

- Monitors log directory health, recovery progress, and offline directories.
- Provides insight into log cleaner efficiency, buffer utilization, and partition cleanliness.
- Tracks cleaner manager activity, dead threads, and time since the last cleaning cycle.
- Surfaces log flush behavior, including flush rate, duration

query.esql:
from metrics-*
| where data_stream.dataset == "kafka.log_manager" and kafka.log_manager.directory_offline_count.log_directory is not null
| stats offline_count = avg(kafka.log_manager.directory_offline_count.value) by kafka.log_manager.directory_offline_count.log_directory
| eval status = case(offline_count == 0, "Online", "Offline")
| rename kafka.log_manager.directory_offline_count.log_directory as Log_Directory, status  as Status
| keep Log_Directory, Status
